whereas.text:
Whereas fathers play an important role in teaching their
			 children life lessons and preparing them to succeed in school and in
			 life;

Whereas children with involved fathers are more likely to
			 do well in school, have a better sense of well-being, and have fewer behavioral
			 problems;

Whereas, when fathers are actively involved in the
			 upbringing of children, the children demonstrate greater self-control and a
			 greater ability to take initiative;
